No fewer than 13,000 job seekers have applied for recruitment into the Western Nigeria Security Network, codenamed Operation Amotekun Corps, in Osun State. The Director-General of the Corps in the state, Comrade Amitolu Shittu, made this known on Wednesday in Osogbo. The state governor, Adegboyega Oyetola had on Monday, June 15, directed that recruitment into the Amotekun Corps should commence. The time limit for application, which elapsed last Friday, was later extended till Tuesday. 